    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 4: Singularity Spectrum f(α)\n",
    "\n",
    "Via **Legendre transform**:\n",
    "- α = dτ/dq (Hölder exponents)\n",
    "- f(α) = qα - τ(q) (fractal dimensions)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Interpretation**:\n",
    "- Wide spectrum → high multifractality\n",
    "- Narrow spectrum → low multifractality\n",
    "- Point → monofractal\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compute singularity spectrum\n",
    "print(\"Computing singularity spectrum...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_singularity_spectrum(q_values, tau_q):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Compute singularity spectrum f(α) via Legendre transform.\"\"\"\n",
    "    # Numerical derivative\n",
    "    dq = q_values[1] - q_values[0]\n",
    "    alpha = np.gradient(tau_q, dq)\n",
    "    f_alpha = q_values * alpha - tau_q\n",
    "    return alpha, f_alpha\n",
    "\n",
    "alpha_mono, f_alpha_mono = compute_singularity_spectrum(q_values, tau_mono)\n",
    "alpha_multi, f_alpha_multi = compute_singularity_spectrum(q_values, tau_multi)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Spectrum properties\n",
    "width_alpha_mono = alpha_mono.max() - alpha_mono.min()\n",
    "width_alpha_multi = alpha_multi.max() - alpha_multi.min()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Singularity Spectrum Analysis:\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMonofractal:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  α range: [{alpha_mono.min():.3f}, {alpha_mono.max():.3f}]\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Δα = {width_alpha_mono:.3f} (narrow spectrum)\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMultifractal:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  α range: [{alpha_multi.min():.3f}, {alpha_multi.max():.3f}]\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Δα = {width_alpha_multi:.3f} (broad spectrum)\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\n💡 Spectrum width ratio: {width_alpha_multi / width_alpha_mono:.2f}x\")"
   ]
  },
